node.title: "Tinder Swindler" accuser speaks out against alleged con man
node.description: Cecilie Fjellhoy is one of three women whose stories are told in the hit Netflix documentary "Tinder Swindler." All three say they met Shimon Hayut on Tinder and were conned by him.

node.title: Dog missing for 12 years is reunited with family
node.description: "Honestly, I'm in shock. I definitely didn't expect this to ever happen, so I'm really excited. Excited to hopefully bring her back, get her healthy and live the rest of her life," Zoey's owner said.

node.title: Homeowners wrestle with unsettled quake claims 11 years on
node.description: On the 11th anniversary of the Christchurch earthquake, a lawyer dealing with outstanding insurance claims says the city still has a long way to go.

node.title: Paul Farmer, global health care pioneer, dies at 62
node.description: Samantha Power, the former U.S. ambassador to the United Nations, tweeted that Farmer was "a giant" in his field.

node.title: 'Going to be disruptive': Lab worker tests positive to Covid-19
node.description: New Zealand Institute of Medical Laboratory Science president Terry Taylor says while the absence of one from the team will affect capacity, colleagues will fill in the gaps as best they could.

node.title: Queen tests positive for Covid-19
node.description: The Queen has tested positive for Covid but has mild symptoms and expects to continue "light duties" at Windsor, Buckingham Palace says.

node.title: South Auckland church steps up for at-risk families struggling to self-isolate
node.description: With cases of Omicron accelerating at an alarming rate, one South Auckland reverend is calling on fellow ministers to put their hands up to help those needing to self-isolate.

node.title: Police investigate Hamilton death as homicide
node.description: Police have launched a homicide investigation after the death of a man in Hamilton last night.

node.title: Victims of Islamophobic attack await news on disciplinary action
node.description: The families of the victims of an Islamophobic assault at a Dunedin school have not been told of the discipline the attackers will face, the Otago Muslim Association says.

node.title: Northland DHB braces for field hospital, Covid-19 influx
node.description: Omicron patients will go to a makeshift facility if Covid-19 cases take up too many beds at Whangārei Hospital.

node.title: Bride's uncle killed by officer at wedding reception, family says
node.description: "His niece's wedding was the first day he was able to come out and celebrate in a long time," the family said.

node.title: Icahn hits McDonald's over "unnecessary suffering" of pigs
node.description: Billionaire mogul has a reputation for being ruthless, but says his fight with fast-food chain has nothing to do with money.

node.title: Are there lessons for NZ from Canada's protest crackdown?
node.description: Opinion - The de-escalation strategy of Canadian police didn't shift the protesters in Ottawa. With public confidence in the New Zealand police on the line, the political ramifications are serious…

node.title: SpaceX launches 46 more Starlink internet satellites
node.description: The California rocket builder has now launched 2,137 Starlinks as it populates a global network.

node.title: Own goals cost Football Ferns
node.description: The Football Ferns have been outclassed 5-0 by the United States in their latest game at a four-nation tournament in California.

node.title: Bank of America CEO: "It's time" for Fed to hike interest rates
node.description: Strong consumer spending and economic data show that Fed needs to start raising interest rates, BofA chief said.

node.title: Putin says he may recognize Ukraine breakaway regions "today"
node.description: Russia's leader appears to be following steps for an invasion of Ukraine that the U.S. not only predicted, but warned the world to watch for less than a week ago.

node.title: Ukrainians on edge as fighting escalates with Russian-backed rebels
node.description: There's some hope with the prospect of a Biden-Putin summit, but after a weekend of dramatic developments, calm is giving way to concern.

node.title: Drop in infant formula sales hits A2 Milk's bottom line
node.description: Pandemic volatility and tough market conditions in China have seen the specialty dairy company's half-year profits halved.

node.title: Woman accidentally killed by 17-year-old hunting for wild boar
node.description: The incident has rekindled debate over a tradition that critics say needs more strict regulation.

node.title: Trump's GOP critics to gather in Washington with an eye on 2024
node.description: On the same weekend as the CPAC gathering, Trump critics will cheer on the two Republicans on the select committee probing January 6, Liz Cheney and Adam Kinzinger.

node.title: Biden-Putin summit on the table — if Russia doesn't invade Ukraine
node.description: Kremlin confirms interest in a possible presidential summit as the U.S. warns Putin's forces are "continuing preparations for a full-scale assault."

node.title: Man arrested 35 years after woman found dead by her husband
node.description: Terry Wood found his wife dead, with her throat cut, in the kitchen of their Niles Township home after returning from going bowling.

node.title: U.S. claims Russia has list of Ukrainians to target after invasion
node.description: "The United States is gravely concerned that a further Russian invasion of Ukraine would produce widespread human suffering," U.S. Ambassador Bathsheba Nell Crocker warned.

node.title: More teachers think about leaving as shortages rise and demands grow
node.description: "If you asked me if I'll be in the classroom in two years, or three years, I say those odds are even lower," one teacher said.

node.title: $200,000 reward offered in case of girl who disappeared from playground
node.description: She was last seen in the playground of an apartment complex in San Antonio on December 20. Her mother walked away briefly, and returned to discover her child missing.

node.title: Russia launching "brutal war of choice" if Ukraine invaded, Sullivan says
node.description: National security adviser tells "CBS Mornings" that the world will hold Russia accountable should Putin order an invasion of Ukraine.

node.title: U.K. music entrepreneur Jamal Edwards dies at 31
node.description: The founder of SBTV helped launch the career of notable British music artists, including rapper Dave and Ed Sheeran.

node.title: Wolves competing with bears for food has unexpected results
node.description: When a bear steals a meal from a wolf pack, the wolves kill less often, researcher say.

node.title: Skydiving instructor dies day after chute doesn't open during jump
node.description: A witness said a second chute did open, but only partially. The instructor's company said a student with him during the tandem jump has serious but non-life-threatening injuries.
